cdx6500PPCTX25PortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTX25PortTable
cdx6500PPCTX25PortTable.description: A table of X.25 Port configuration entries.

cdx6500PPCTX25PortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTX25PortEntry
cdx6500PPCTX25PortEntry.description: An X.25 Configuration Table entry. Each entry contains the configuration parameters for a single X.25 port.

cdx6500X25CfgPortNumber.name: cdx6500X25CfgPortNumber
cdx6500X25CfgPortNumber.description: Port number for this X.25 port.

cdx6500X25CfgConnType.name: cdx6500X25CfgConnType
cdx6500X25CfgConnType.description: Specify the control signal handshake and clocking required for a connection to be made to this port: simp - simple, no control signals required. dtr - dedicated, require the data terminal ready signal (DTR). dtrd - same as DTR, except data set ready (DSR) drops between calls. dimo - port handshakes with attached dial modem dimoa - same as DIMO except DSR never raised on incoming call from modem. dimob - same as DIMO except DSR follows DTR on incoming call from modem. dimov - port handshakes with attached V.25 bis dial modem. emri - port emulates a dial modem with ring indicator (RI). emdc - port emulates a dial modem with data carrier detect (DCD). simpv - SIMP/DIMOv, modem will switch from Leased to Dial-only mode when leased line goes down (used with Link Backup only). simpb - simple, no control signals required for data transmission and reception. By default output leads will be low.

cdx6500X25CfgPortCont.name: cdx6500X25CfgPortCont
cdx6500X25CfgPortCont.description: Specify any of the following port control options: NONE - no option specified. MB - raise Pin 22 when the port becomes disabled.

cdx6500X25CfgClockSource.name: cdx6500X25CfgClockSource
cdx6500X25CfgClockSource.description: int - internal clock source. ext - external clock source. extint - internal receive and external transmit clock source (DCE only). extlp - external receive and loopback transmit clock source (DTE only). extlp must be configured in conjunction with extint.

cdx6500X25CfgClockSpeed.name: cdx6500X25CfgClockSpeed
cdx6500X25CfgClockSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second, when using internal clocking. The highest available speed is dependant on the card type, and on the interface type. See the 6500 Series Configuration and Administration Manual for proper values.

cdx6500X25CfgAdmnInterfaceMode.name: cdx6500X25CfgAdmnInterfaceMode
cdx6500X25CfgAdmnInterfaceMode.description: The logical link address must be set to complementary values in devices at each end of the link: dte - link to have logical DTE address (A). dce - link to have logical DCE address (B). negotiate - link ends will negotiate which end is DCE address (B). This option is available only if the correct CSK is enabled.

cdx6500X25CfgAdmnNumberPVCs.name: cdx6500X25CfgAdmnNumberPVCs
cdx6500X25CfgAdmnNumberPVCs.description: Number of logical channels used for Permanent Virtual Circuits. The total number of PVC and SVC channels on a link should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs. PVC connections must be configured in the PVC Table.

cdx6500X25CfgStartPVCChanNum.name: cdx6500X25CfgStartPVCChanNum
cdx6500X25CfgStartPVCChanNum.description: This is the starting logical channel number for the Permanent Virtual Circuits on this link. Not used if the number of PVCs = 0.

cdx6500X25CfgNumberSVCs.name: cdx6500X25CfgNumberSVCs
cdx6500X25CfgNumberSVCs.description: Number of logical channels used in Switched Virtual Circuits. The total number of PVC and SVC channels on a link should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs.

cdx6500X25CfgStartSVCChanNum.name: cdx6500X25CfgStartSVCChanNum
cdx6500X25CfgStartSVCChanNum.description: This is the starting logical channel number for the Switched Virtual Circuits on this link. Not used if the number of SVCs = 0.

cdx6500X25CfgInitFrame.name: cdx6500X25CfgInitFrame
cdx6500X25CfgInitFrame.description: Specify the initial frame required by other end for link startup: none - do nothing (other end initiates link-up). sabm - send SABM. disc - send DISC, then SABM.

cdx6500X25CfgT1RetryTimer.name: cdx6500X25CfgT1RetryTimer
cdx6500X25CfgT1RetryTimer.description: T1 link retry timer value in tenths of a second (e.g. 30 = 3.0 seconds).

cdx6500X25CfgT4PollTimer.name: cdx6500X25CfgT4PollTimer
cdx6500X25CfgT4PollTimer.description: This sets the time an idle link is probed for assurance of connection to the remote device. 0 - disable the timer X - X is in tenths of a second (e.g. 40 = 4.0 seconds) and must be set greater than T1.

cdx6500X25CfgN2TransTries.name: cdx6500X25CfgN2TransTries
cdx6500X25CfgN2TransTries.description: The maximum number of attempts allowed to complete a transmission.

cdx6500X25CfgFrameSeqCounting.name: cdx6500X25CfgFrameSeqCounting
cdx6500X25CfgFrameSeqCounting.description: Port uses normal or extended frame sequence numbering norm - normal sequence counting (Modulo 8). ext - extended sequencing (Modulo 128).

cdx6500X25CfgKFrameWindow.name: cdx6500X25CfgKFrameWindow
cdx6500X25CfgKFrameWindow.description: Frame level window size must be set to the same value in devices at each end of the link.

cdx6500X25CfgAdmnPacketSequencing.name: cdx6500X25CfgAdmnPacketSequencing
cdx6500X25CfgAdmnPacketSequencing.description: Port uses normal or extended packet level sequence numbers : norm - normal sequencing (Modulo 8). ext - extended sequencing (Modulo 128). The value must be the same in devices at each end of the link.

cdx6500X25CfgWPacketWindow.name: cdx6500X25CfgWPacketWindow
cdx6500X25CfgWPacketWindow.description: Packet level window size must be set to the same value in devices at each end of the link.

cdx6500X25CfgPPacketSize.name: cdx6500X25CfgPPacketSize
cdx6500X25CfgPPacketSize.description: This is the maximum packet size used on X.25 links. For proper operation, the size must be the same in devices at each end of the link.

cdx6500X25CfgMaxNegotPacketSize.name: cdx6500X25CfgMaxNegotPacketSize
cdx6500X25CfgMaxNegotPacketSize.description: This is the maximum negotiated packet size allowed for inbound and outbound calls on this X.25 link.

cdx6500X25CfgDataQueueUpper.name: cdx6500X25CfgDataQueueUpper
cdx6500X25CfgDataQueueUpper.description: This is the maximum number of data packets a channel on this port will queue for transmission before invoking flow control to the attached channel

cdx6500X25CfgDataQueueLower.name: cdx6500X25CfgDataQueueLower
cdx6500X25CfgDataQueueLower.description: This is the number of data packets a channel on this port will have queued for transmission when it releases flow control to the attached channel

cdx6500X25CfgAdmnRestartTimer.name: cdx6500X25CfgAdmnRestartTimer
cdx6500X25CfgAdmnRestartTimer.description: Restart-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires, request is sent again.

cdx6500X25CfgAdmnResetTimer.name: cdx6500X25CfgAdmnResetTimer
cdx6500X25CfgAdmnResetTimer.description: Reset-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires, request is sent again.

cdx6500X25CfgAdmnCallTimer.name: cdx6500X25CfgAdmnCallTimer
cdx6500X25CfgAdmnCallTimer.description: Call-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires, call is cleared.

cdx6500X25CfgAdmnClearTimer.name: cdx6500X25CfgAdmnClearTimer
cdx6500X25CfgAdmnClearTimer.description: Clear-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires, request is sent again.

cdx6500X25CfgOutDelFacilities.name: cdx6500X25CfgOutDelFacilities
cdx6500X25CfgOutDelFacilities.description: Specify facilities deleted from an outbound call before it is forwarded: NONE - no facilities deleted. THRO - delete throughput class negotiation. NUI - delete network user identification. CUG - delete closed user group. Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. THRO+NUI. . .).

cdx6500X25CfgOutAddFacilities.name: cdx6500X25CfgOutAddFacilities
cdx6500X25CfgOutAddFacilities.description: Specify facilities added to an outbound call before it is forwarded: NONE - no facilities added. REV - add reverse charging. PACK - add packet size negotiation. WIND - add window size negotiation. Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. PACK+WIND+. . .).

cdx6500X25CfgOutBarFacilities.name: cdx6500X25CfgOutBarFacilities
cdx6500X25CfgOutBarFacilities.description: Specify facilities which, if present in an outbound call will be blocked by the port: NONE - no facility blocked. REV - bar reverse charging. FAST - bar fast select. BCUG - bar Bilateral Closed User Group. DGRAM - bar datagram. Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. REV+FAST).

cdx6500X25CfgInBarFacilities.name: cdx6500X25CfgInBarFacilities
cdx6500X25CfgInBarFacilities.description: Specify facilities which, if present in an inbound call, will be blocked by the port: NONE - no facility blocked. BCUG - bar Bilateral Closed User Group. DGRAM - bar datagram. REV - bar Reverse Charging. Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. DGRAM+BCUG).

cdx6500X25CfgOptions.name: cdx6500X25CfgOptions
cdx6500X25CfgOptions.description: Select options on this X.25 port as follows: NONE - no option specified. 1980 - use X.25 1980. NUI - perform network user identification validation check. PDN - connected to Public Data Network. CUD - use call user data subaddressing. IBAR - bar all calls coming in from X.25 port user. OBAR - bar all calls going out to X.25 port user. CBCK - allow routing inbound calls back out this port. CUG - check closed user group; otherwise, CUG passes transparently. CAUSE - pass cause, diagnostic, code in outbound packets. HOLD - hold calls over link restart. NRST - do not send restart packet on link-up. BKUP - this is a backup port to be activated if other ports are down. INL - inter-node link. Link goes to another Vanguard device.INL may be a poor choice for high speed links.INLB is set with INL to improve the performance of high speed links.INLB can be configured in the More X25 Options parameter. INLA - set with INL option when an X.25 link connection is to a 6500 node using 2.12.04 or earlier. DELAY - enable Delay and Path trace on this link (link must connected to Rel. 4.xx node). Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. 1980+NUI+. . .).

cdx6500X25CfgNumRoutDigits.name: cdx6500X25CfgNumRoutDigits
cdx6500X25CfgNumRoutDigits.description: This specifies the number of routing digits in the call user data. It is used on X.25 links attached to a Public Data Network where the private network address is carried in the call user data.

cdx6500X25CfgPortDigitsToStrip.name: cdx6500X25CfgPortDigitsToStrip
cdx6500X25CfgPortDigitsToStrip.description: For X.25 links connected to a Public Data Network, this parameter specifies the number of prefix digits to remove from the called address before forwarding the call to the PDN.

cdx6500X25CfgInDigitsToStrip.name: cdx6500X25CfgInDigitsToStrip
cdx6500X25CfgInDigitsToStrip.description: For X.25 links connected to a Public Data Network, this parameter specifies the number of prefix digits to remove from the incoming calling address before forwarding the call from the PDN.

cdx6500X25CfgRestrictConn.name: cdx6500X25CfgRestrictConn
cdx6500X25CfgRestrictConn.description: All calls entering this port will be routed to the destination specified in this parameter, irrespective of route selection table entries. Blank this field to disable this function.

cdx6500X25CfgPortAddress.name: cdx6500X25CfgPortAddress
cdx6500X25CfgPortAddress.description: On X.25 links: If the X.25 Option REGO or REGI is selected, this address is inserted into the calling address field of the outbound or inbound call packet. On MUX links: When a MUX channel makes a call, the subaddress of the channel is appended to this address and inserted into the calling address field of the call packet.

cdx6500X25CfgCUGMember.name: cdx6500X25CfgCUGMember
cdx6500X25CfgCUGMember.description: The port may be a member of up to 8 different Closed User Groups (CUGs). Each CUG membership must be a two digit number (except `--') and separated by a comma. ( e.g. 12,34,56,09,02,03 ). `--' - No CUG Membership. 00-99 - CUG Membership.

cdx6500X25CfgBillRec.name: cdx6500X25CfgBillRec
cdx6500X25CfgBillRec.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this port.

cdx6500X25CfgSubAddrSize.name: cdx6500X25CfgSubAddrSize
cdx6500X25CfgSubAddrSize.description: For ports connected to a Public Data Network, this parameter specifies the number of digits in the subaddress of an X.25 address.

cdx6500X25CfgIdleDiscTimer.name: cdx6500X25CfgIdleDiscTimer
cdx6500X25CfgIdleDiscTimer.description: The time in seconds that the port must be idle (no calls) before being automatically disconnected. A value of 0 disables the Idle Disconnect feature. This feature may only be enabled on DIMO/DIMOa/DIMOb/DIMOv/SIMPv ports with the BKUP option selected.

cdx6500X25CfgCallSecurity.name: cdx6500X25CfgCallSecurity
cdx6500X25CfgCallSecurity.description: For ports used as V.25 bis backup, this parameter specifies the type of call security to use prior to the link being detected up : disable - Disable will allow both incoming and outgoing calls. enable - Enable will allow ONLY outgoing calls. Incoming calls will be immediately terminated. This parameter is only used with Link Backup.

cdx6500X25CfgProtectLevel.name: cdx6500X25CfgProtectLevel
cdx6500X25CfgProtectLevel.description: This specifies the level of data or connection protection which will be applied to calls to or from this port. The actual level for a call will be negotiated to the lesser of this level and the level configured for the other end of the call : none - No protection. cpOnly - Connection protection only. fullDcp - Full data and connection protection.

cdx6500X25CfgReconnTimeout.name: cdx6500X25CfgReconnTimeout
cdx6500X25CfgReconnTimeout.description: This specifies the number of seconds that DCP on the originating side will wait between reconnection attempts.

cdx6500X25CfgReconnTriesLimit.name: cdx6500X25CfgReconnTriesLimit
cdx6500X25CfgReconnTriesLimit.description: This specifies the number of times that DCP on the originating side will attempt to reconnect before clearing the call. If 0 is entered, it will not attempt to reconnect.

cdx6500X25CfgFacilSubscripCont.name: cdx6500X25CfgFacilSubscripCont
cdx6500X25CfgFacilSubscripCont.description: NONE - Subscription to facilities not enforced. FCN-ON - Flow Control Negotiation enabled. Packet and Window size negotiation facilities in an inbound call will be allowed. Packet and Window size facilities will always be included in outbound calls and call accepted/ connected when this parameter is set. FCN-OFF - Flow Control Negotiation disabled. Inbound calls containing Packet and Window size facilities will be cleared. Packet and Window size facilities will not be present in outbound calls and call accepted/ connected when this parameter is set. TCN-ON - Throughput Class Negotiation enabled. The throughput class negotiation facility in an inbound call will be allowed. The throughput class negotiation facility will always be included in outbound calls and call accepted/connected when this parameter is set. The facility is passed onward to the destination in the call packet transparently and does not alter the handling of the SVC data within the node. TCN-OFF - Throughput Class Negotiation disabled. Inbound calls containing the throughput class negotiation facility will be cleared. The throughput class negotiation facility will not be present in outbound calls and call accepted/connected when this parameter is set. Some combinations of above options are allowed (e.g. FCN-ON+TCN-ON).

cdx6500X25CfgAlarmPriority.name: cdx6500X25CfgAlarmPriority
cdx6500X25CfgAlarmPriority.description: Specify the severity level of LINK UP and LINK DOWN alarms : network - Severity HIGH alarms will be generated. access - Severity LOW alarms will be generated.

cdx6500X25CfgAddrTrans.name: cdx6500X25CfgAddrTrans
cdx6500X25CfgAddrTrans.description: Select any of the following address translation options NONE - no option specified Outbound Call Processing: DEDO - delete called address. DEGO - delete calling address. REGO - replace calling address with configured Port Address. REGSO - replace calling address with configured Port Address plus Inbound Subaddress obtained from the Inbound Call Translation Table entry where Private Network Address matches the entire calling address. INGO - replace calling address with configured Port Address and retain original calling subaddress. SAGO - strip calling address, but retain subaddress. Inbound Call Processing: INGI - replace calling address with configured Port Address and retain original calling subaddress. REGI - replace calling address with configured Port Address. SRGI - select route from the Calling Address Translation Table by replacing the called address with the Private Network Address where the Inbound Calling Address matches the beginning of the calling address. Call Accept Processing: DADA - delete called address in inbound/outbound call accept. DAGA - delete calling address in inbound/outbound call accept. IADD - copy called and calling addresses from call request into outbound call accepted/connected. Some of the options may be combined (e.g. DEDO+DEGO+...)

cdx6500X25CfgNumberInSVCs.name: cdx6500X25CfgNumberInSVCs
cdx6500X25CfgNumberInSVCs.description: Number of logical channels used in One Way Incoming Switched Virtual Circuits. The total number of PVC, One Way Incoming, One Way Outgoing and Two Way SVC channels should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs.

cdx6500X25CfgStartInSVCChanNum.name: cdx6500X25CfgStartInSVCChanNum
cdx6500X25CfgStartInSVCChanNum.description: This is the starting logical channel number for the One Way Incoming Switched Virtual Circuits on this link. Not used if the number of One Way Incoming SVCs = 0.

cdx6500X25CfgNumberOutSVCs.name: cdx6500X25CfgNumberOutSVCs
cdx6500X25CfgNumberOutSVCs.description: Number of logical channels used in One Way Outgoing Switched Virtual Circuits. The total number of PVC, One Way Outgoing, One Way Outgoing and Two Way SVC channels should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs.

cdx6500X25CfgStartOutSVCChanNum.name: cdx6500X25CfgStartOutSVCChanNum
cdx6500X25CfgStartOutSVCChanNum.description: This is the starting logical channel number for the One Way Outgoing Switched Virtual Circuits on this link. Not used if the number of One Way Outgoing SVCs = 0.

cdx6500X25CfgChargeInfoReq.name: cdx6500X25CfgChargeInfoReq
cdx6500X25CfgChargeInfoReq.description: This parameter specifies whether Charging Information has to be sent even without requesting.

cdx6500X25CfgVerfnTimer.name: cdx6500X25CfgVerfnTimer
cdx6500X25CfgVerfnTimer.description: Specify the NUI verification timer in seconds. The call is cleared if timer expires.

cdx6500X25CfgValdFailures.name: cdx6500X25CfgValdFailures
cdx6500X25CfgValdFailures.description: The maximum number of successive NUI verification failures an X.25 DTE can tolerate when making verification attempts timer expires.

cdx6500X25CfgActionType.name: cdx6500X25CfgActionType
cdx6500X25CfgActionType.description: This specifies the course of action to be taken if the NUI violations exceed the configured threshold count. This parameter is effective only if the X25 options parameter is set to CNUI NONE - No action is taken. DISC - All connections on the port are broken. DEGR - Port is busied-out for one minute then it is re-enabled. LOCK - All connections on the port are broken and the port is disabled.

cdx6500X25CfgLineIdleMode.name: cdx6500X25CfgLineIdleMode
cdx6500X25CfgLineIdleMode.description: Specify any of the following line idle mode options: FLAG - Flag fill between frames MARK - Mark idle between frames

cdx6500X25CfgConfOption.name: cdx6500X25CfgConfOption
cdx6500X25CfgConfOption.description: Select any of the following conformance control options: NONE - no option specified CHKFAC - Checking of facility codes enabled.

cdx6500X25CfgInvertTxClk.name: cdx6500X25CfgInvertTxClk
cdx6500X25CfgInvertTxClk.description: This parameter specifies whether the phase of the transmit clock should be inverted. NO - Don't invert YES - Invert

cdx6500X25CfgDimType.name: cdx6500X25CfgDimType
cdx6500X25CfgDimType.description: Specify the physical interface type to be used for this port: V.36 - V.36 physical interface EIA-530A - EIA-530A physical interface V.35 - V.35 physical interface X.21 - X.21 physical interface RS-449 - RS-449 physical interface EIA-530 - EIA-530 physical interface RS-232 - RS-232 physical interface

cdx6500X25CfgMoreOptions.name: cdx6500X25CfgMoreOptions
cdx6500X25CfgMoreOptions.description: Select more options on this X.25 port as follows: NONE - no option specified INLB - set with INL option to improve performance if inter-node link is a high speed link

cdx6500X25CfgPsfFlag.name: cdx6500X25CfgPsfFlag
cdx6500X25CfgPsfFlag.description: Enable or Disable Port Selection Facility feature. Used to control access to ports for Select user group applications.

cdx6500X25CfgElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500X25CfgElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500X25CfgElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500X25CfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOptio.name: cdx6500X25CfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500X25CfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOptio.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500X25CfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfac.name: cdx6500X25CfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500X25CfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfac.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500PPSTX25PortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTX25PortTable
cdx6500PPSTX25PortTable.description: A table of X.25 Port statistics.

cdx6500PPSTX25PortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTX25PortEntry
cdx6500PPSTX25PortEntry.description: An X.25 Statistics Table entry. Each entry contains the statistics for a single X.25 port.

cdx6500X25StatPortNumber.name: cdx6500X25StatPortNumber
cdx6500X25StatPortNumber.description: The port number for this X.25 port.

cdx6500X25StatPortStatus.name: cdx6500X25StatPortStatus
cdx6500X25StatPortStatus.description: Status of this port : Up - Port is active Down - Port Is inactive Disabled - An operator has disabled the port Busy Out - an operator has busied out the port

cdx6500X25StatPortState.name: cdx6500X25StatPortState
cdx6500X25StatPortState.description: discPhase - Disconnect Phase. linkDisk - Link Disconnect. linkSetup - The port is sending SABM frames and waiting for a UA response. sabmColl - SABM Collision. frameReject - The port has rejected a received frame. normal - The port sending/receiving data. remoteBusy - The port is receiving RNR frames. reset - The port is being reset. sendRej - The port is sending REJ frames. rbSr - The port is receiving RNR frames and sending REJ frames.

cdx6500X25StatActualPortSpeed.name: cdx6500X25StatActualPortSpeed
cdx6500X25StatActualPortSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port when Clock = INT; this is the detected clock speed if Clock = EXT. If Port Speed is 0, Clock = EXT, but clocking is not being received fom attatched device.

cdx6500X25StatPortUtilIn.name: cdx6500X25StatPortUtilIn
cdx6500X25StatPortUtilIn.description: Percentage of port bandwidth in use.

cdx6500X25StatPortUtilOut.name: cdx6500X25StatPortUtilOut
cdx6500X25StatPortUtilOut.description: Percentage of port bandwidth in use.

cdx6500X25StatMaxSVCCount.name: cdx6500X25StatMaxSVCCount
cdx6500X25StatMaxSVCCount.description: Maximum number of SVCs in use since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatCurrSVCCount.name: cdx6500X25StatCurrSVCCount
cdx6500X25StatCurrSVCCount.description: Current number of SVCs in use.

cdx6500X25StatInChars.name: cdx6500X25StatInChars
cdx6500X25StatInChars.description: Number of characters received since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatOutChars.name: cdx6500X25StatOutChars
cdx6500X25StatOutChars.description: Number of characters sent since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatInPkts.name: cdx6500X25StatInPkts
cdx6500X25StatInPkts.description: Number of packets received since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatOutPkts.name: cdx6500X25StatOutPkts
cdx6500X25StatOutPkts.description: Number of packets sent since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatInDataFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatInDataFrames
cdx6500X25StatInDataFrames.description: Number of frames received since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatOutDataFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatOutDataFrames
cdx6500X25StatOutDataFrames.description: Number of frames sent since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatCharRateIn.name: cdx6500X25StatCharRateIn
cdx6500X25StatCharRateIn.description: Summary of the characters being received by the port.

cdx6500X25StatCharRateOut.name: cdx6500X25StatCharRateOut
cdx6500X25StatCharRateOut.description: Summary of the characters being sent by the port.

cdx6500X25StatPktRateIn.name: cdx6500X25StatPktRateIn
cdx6500X25StatPktRateIn.description: Summary of the packets being received by the port.

cdx6500X25StatPktRateOut.name: cdx6500X25StatPktRateOut
cdx6500X25StatPktRateOut.description: Summary of the packets being sent by the port.

cdx6500X25StatFrameRateIn.name: cdx6500X25StatFrameRateIn
cdx6500X25StatFrameRateIn.description: Summary of the frames being received by the port.

cdx6500X25StatFrameRateOut.name: cdx6500X25StatFrameRateOut
cdx6500X25StatFrameRateOut.description: Summary of the frames being sent by the port.

cdx6500X25StatOverrunErrs.name: cdx6500X25StatOverrunErrs
cdx6500X25StatOverrunErrs.description: Number of Overrun errors since the last node or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatUnderrunErrs.name: cdx6500X25StatUnderrunErrs
cdx6500X25StatUnderrunErrs.description: Number of Underrun errors since the last node or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatCRCErrs.name: cdx6500X25StatCRCErrs
cdx6500X25StatCRCErrs.description: Number of CRC errors since the last node or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatInInfoFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatInInfoFrames
cdx6500X25StatInInfoFrames.description: Number of Info frames received since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatOutInfoFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatOutInfoFrames
cdx6500X25StatOutInfoFrames.description: Number of Info frames sent since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500X25StatInRNRFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatInRNRFrames
cdx6500X25StatInRNRFrames.description: Number of frames received since last node, port or statistics reset indicating RNR.

cdx6500X25StatOutRNRFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatOutRNRFrames
cdx6500X25StatOutRNRFrames.description: Number of frames sent since last node, port or statistics reset indicating RNR.

cdx6500X25StatInRRFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatInRRFrames
cdx6500X25StatInRRFrames.description: Number of frames received since last node, port or statistics reset indicating RR.

cdx6500X25StatOutRRFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatOutRRFrames
cdx6500X25StatOutRRFrames.description: Number of frames sent since last node, port or statistics reset indicating RR.

cdx6500X25StatInREJFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatInREJFrames
cdx6500X25StatInREJFrames.description: Number of frames received since last node, port or statistics reset indicating REJ.

cdx6500X25StatOutREJFrames.name: cdx6500X25StatOutREJFrames
cdx6500X25StatOutREJFrames.description: Number of frames sent since last node, port or statistics reset indicating REJ.
